@startuml health-verification-flow
!include _standard-style.puml

title Health Verification Pre-Prompt Flow (Phase 33)

actor User
participant "Claude Code" as Claude
participant "UserPromptSubmit\nHook" as Hook
participant "health-prompt-hook.js" as HealthHook
participant "Health coordinator\n:3034" as Coord
participant "Probed services\n(dashboard, vkb,\nsemantic-analysis,\nllm-cli-proxy, …)" as Services

User -> Claude: Types prompt
activate Claude

Claude -> Hook: Trigger hook
activate Hook

Hook -> HealthHook: Execute hook script
activate HealthHook

HealthHook -> Coord: GET /health/state
activate Coord
Coord --> HealthHook: state JSON\n(generated_at, services,\ndatabases, lsl_by_project, …)
deactivate Coord

alt generated_at fresh (<3 min)
    HealthHook -> HealthHook: Format compact summary\n("All systems operational")
    HealthHook --> Hook: Return health context
else generated_at stale (>3 min)
    HealthHook --> Hook: Return "[🏥⏰] coordinator stale"\n(operator action required —\nno auto-heal in Phase 33)
end

deactivate HealthHook

Hook --> Claude: Add context to prompt
deactivate Hook

note right of Coord
  The coordinator continuously
  probes services and refreshes
  databases / processes / files
  blocks. The hook only reads
  state — it does not trigger
  remediation.
end note

note over Services
  Probed by the coordinator on
  its own schedule (not by the
  hook). Reachability + latency
  surface in services[*].
end note

Coord -[#orange,dashed]-> Services : probe (independent)

Claude -> Claude: Process prompt with\nhealth context
Claude --> User: Response with health info
deactivate Claude

@enduml
